<paragraph id="541E36C9FFC5FF5D259AFA6AFA11F986" blockId="11.[151,1437,1494,1604]" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">
<keyLead id="EF5095FCFFC5FF5D259AFA6AFA11F986" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">
<keyStep id="EF552E6CFFC5FF5D259AFA6AFA11F986" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">
1. The eyes are small, less than 1/3 of the head height; peduncle and rami of uropods 1–3 with few marginal short spine-like setae (fig. 1a, 3a, b)................................................. 
<taxonomicName id="93A14D4AFFC5FF5D26C7FA48FA11F986" authority="Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks, 1994" authorityName="Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks" authorityYear="1994" box="[970,1436,1523,1545]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pleustidae" genus="Eosymtes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Amphipoda" pageId="11" pageNumber="558" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minutus">
<emphasis id="66D5EADBFFC5FF5D26C7FA48FBFBF987" box="[970,1142,1524,1545]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">Eosymtes minutus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="30304B38FFC5FF5D2171FA4FFA11F986" author="Bousfield, E. L. &amp; Hendrycks, E. A." box="[1148,1436,1523,1545]" pageId="11" pageNumber="558" pagination="17 - 57" refId="ref6232" refString="Bousfield, E. L. &amp; Hendrycks, E. A. (1994) A revision of family Pleustidae (Amphipoda: Gammaridea). Part 1. Systematics and biogeography of component subfamilies. Amphipacifica, 1 (1), 17 - 57." type="journal article" year="1994">Bousfield &amp; Hendrycks, 1994</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</keyStep>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="541E36C9FFC5FF5D259AF9ACFA11F9CD" blockId="11.[151,1437,1494,1604]" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">
<keyLead id="EF5095FCFFC5FF5D259AF9ACFA11F9CD" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">
<keyStep id="EF552E6CFFC5FF5D259AF9ACFA11F9CD" pageId="11" pageNumber="558">
